Package: pvars
Type: Package
Title: VAR Modeling for Heterogeneous Panels
Version: 0.1
Author: Lennart Empting [aut, cre, cph]
Authors@R: c(person("Lennart", "Empting", role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"), email = "lennart.empting@vwl.uni-due.de"))
Maintainer: Lennart Empting <lennart.empting@vwl.uni-due.de>
Description: Implements (1) panel cointegration rank tests, (2) estimators for panels of VAR, and (3) panel-based identification methods for structural vector autoregressive (SVAR) models, allowing for cross-sectional dependence in the error terms and for structural breaks in the deterministic terms of the VAR processes.
Depends: R (>= 3.5.0), svars (>= 1.3.4)
Imports: stats, utils, MASS, expm, clue, copula, DEoptim, steadyICA, pbapply, vars, scales, ggplot2, reshape2
Suggests: testthat (>= 2.1.0), urca, plm, panelvar, ggfortify, tikzDevice, RColorBrewer
License: MIT + file LICENSE
LazyData: TRUE
NeedsCompilation: no
RoxygenNote: 7.3.2
Encoding: UTF-8
URL: https://github.com/Lenni89/pvars
BugReports: https://github.com/Lenni89/pvars/issues
